Reasoning: 
- cs.CV (Computer Vision) is the most likely category as the paper deals with depth estimation and visual odometry from video frames.
- cs.RO (Robotics) is also likely as visual odometry is an important component in robotics and the paper proposes a method for estimating it.
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is another likely category as the paper proposes a learning-based method using Recurrent Neural Networks.
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is also possible as the paper proposes a method for estimating depth and visual odometry, which are important components in AI applications such as autonomous driving.
- cs.CVPR (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is a sub-category of cs.CV and is also possible as the paper proposes a method for depth estimation and visual odometry, which are important topics in CVPR.
